    <aside><title>Expand part c</title>
          <p>
            What happens as <m>x</m> gets closer and closer
            (but not equal)
            to <m>a = 1</m>?
            Does the function <m>g(x)</m> get as close as we would like to a single value?
          </p>
              <textInput name="limitDNE" expanded/>
          
          <conditionalContent condition="$limitDNE.value!=$blank and $limat2.creditAchieved=1">

    <aside>
  <title>Check your answer</title>
          <p>
            The function does not get closer and closer to a single value. From the left side, or x-values less than 1, the function is approaching 3, while from the right side, or x-values greater than 1, the function is approaching 2.  </p>
      <p> Note that the function was approaching a single number at <m>x=2</m> from both sides, even though there was a hole right at <m>x=2</m>.</p>
